1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In today's session we will discuss choosing and installing the right theme for you.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Here are the learning objectives for this workshop.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
To differentiate between the four different types of themes,

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
to find and evaluate themes,

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,000
to install and update your theme and lastly to access support for your theme.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Let's get going.

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,000
In short, a theme is basically a website template with a certain layout and design.

8
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
When you use WordPress, your content is completely separated from its presentation.

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
This means that the look and feel of your site can change completely by just using a different theme,

10
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
while your content will remain the same.

11
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Let's look at an example.

12
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Here I am using the Twenty Twent-Three default theme.

13
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
And in the next example, I have installed and activated the Bounce theme,

14
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,000
which has a very different look and feel to it.

15
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
But the content remains the same.

16
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:04,000
It is also important to highlight that your site won't look the same as the thumbnail or example pages of the theme you install and activate.

17
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,000
It is merely an example of what can be achieved and sometimes require specific plugins to be installed to achieve the initial appearance.

18
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,000
There are thousands of free themes available in WordPress,

19
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,000
but there are also premium themes available outside of the theme repository.

20
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
But please take note, many free versions also offer premium packages.

21
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
You might be asking, what type of themes are there?

22
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
There are four types of themes to take note of.

23
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Block themes, classic themes, hybrid themes and universal themes.

24
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,000
It might be helpful to mention that block themes and classic themes are most commonly used,

25
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
and that block themes are the future of WordPress.

26
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Let's then start by looking at block themes.

27
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
A block theme uses blocks for all parts of the site,

28
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,000
including navigation menus, headers, content and footers.

29
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Block themes allow you to edit and customize all parts of your site within the Site Editor.

30
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Let's see a block theme in action.

31
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,000
I will make my way to Appearance and click on Themes.

32
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
I have activated a block based theme called Twenty Twenty-Three,

33
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,000
and in the left sidebar you will notice we have access to the Editor.

34
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
If we click on Editor, we will be taken to the Site Editor,

35
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
and here you are able to create and edit pages.

36
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:48,000
You can create a draft page or edit one of your existing pages.

37
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Next, we can also change the site-wide styles of our site,

38
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
or we can customize the appearance of specific blocks for the whole site.

39
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
The Site Editor also allows you to set up templates.

40
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,000
You can add new templates or edit the templates that come with your theme.

41
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
And lastly, you can also manage a variety of patterns,

42
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:27,000
patterns that you have created yourself or header and footer template patterns

43
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,000
that we of course add to templates.

44
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
I realize that some folks might be unfamiliar with terms like styles, templates, etc.

45
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,000
So please check out the resources below this video to learn more.

46
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:44,000
There is also a wonderful new feature that allows you to preview a block theme before switching.

47
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,000
When you hover over the block theme, you will see a button live preview.

48
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
When you click on Live preview, you will be taken into the Site Editor.

49
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,000
So not only are you able to preview the site, but you also get a taste of the Site Editor.

50
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,000
And now you can go ahead and make any changes or customizations as you please.

51
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,000
I will for example change the style variation and also change the font of the text.

52
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,000
And now we can explore our pages, our templates, etc.

53
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
And if you like what you see, you even have the option to activate and save the theme and the changes you have made.

54
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,000
A classic theme does not use the block editor to manage the site layout beyond posts and pages.

55
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,000
These use the Customizer, menus and widgets to make changes to theme settings.

56
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:58,000
And since classic themes have been around the longest, there are many more to choose from.

57
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Let's take a closer look at an example of a classic theme.

58
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,000
When we make our way to Appearance and click on Themes, you will notice I have activated the Twenty Sixteen theme.

59
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:14,000
And in the sidebar settings, you will have access to the Customizer and more.

60
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,000
And when you open the Customizer, you will be able to change all your theme settings from here.

61
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,000
And note, block themes on the other hand provide greater flexibility for designing and customizing your website.

62
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,000
A hybrid theme is a classic theme that adopts some features of site editing, like the Template Editor.

63
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:42,000
A hybrid theme such as Eksell still uses the Customizer to make changes, while also being able to create your own custom templates.

64
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,000
So let's make our way to pages, open one of your pages and go to the sidebar settings on the right.

65
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Click on Templates and you are able to assign a page to a different template or create a custom template.

66
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:14,000
And lastly, a universal theme is a theme that can be configured completely either way, as a block theme or classic theme.

67
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:22,000
In this example, I have installed the universal theme Emulsion and as you will notice, you have access to the Customizer as well as the Editor.

68
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Next, let's talk about searching and adding a new theme.

69
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:39,000
To add a new theme, go to Appearance and click on Themes. And at the top, click on Add new.

70
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:47,000
You can search for the most popular themes, the latest themes that's been added and there's even a designated area for block themes.

71
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:56,000
When you click on a theme, you will be able to see more details about the theme as well as a preview.

72
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,000
When you click on Feature filter, you will be able to search for themes according to subject, features and layout.

73
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:15,000
What makes a good theme?

74
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:18,000
To review a theme, make your way to WordPress.org, hover over Download and Extend and then click on Themes.

75
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,000
Here you can search for a variety of themes.

76
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Once you find the theme you are looking for, click on More info to find out more about the specific theme.

77
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:37,000
On the right hand side, you will find all the information you need to make an informed decision.

78
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,000
When you look at the version updates, active installations and ratings, it will give you a good sense of the overall experience others have had with this theme.

79
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,000
How do I install a theme?

80
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,000
To install a new theme, make your way to Appearance, click on Themes and select Add new.

81
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:02,000
Once you find the theme you are looking for, click on Install.

82
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:08,000
And once installed, don't forget to click on Activate.

83
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
If you have a theme in the form of a zip file, you can install it manually.

84
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:19,000
Click on Add new and then at the top, select Upload theme.

85
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:24,000
And then you can upload it from your computer.

86
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,000
What about updates?

87
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:33,000
If there are updates available, you will be notified in the top menu bar as well as the dashboard menu.

88
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:39,000
You can navigate to the updates page and scroll down.

89
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:47,000
And here you will find a single theme or a list of themes that have updates available.

90
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,000
And from this page, you can choose to update individual themes or all at once.

91
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Remember to back up your site before making any updates or you can consider using a child theme.

92
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:04,000
A child theme is a sub theme that inherits the looking feel of the main theme and all of its functions.

93
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Using a child theme lets you upgrade the parent theme without affecting the customizations you have made to your site.

94
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:18,000
Customizations are kept separate from the main theme's files.

95
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:21,000
But I will add a link to this in the resources below.

96
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:24,000
Another option is to make your way to Appearance, click on Themes and go to the theme that needs to be updated.

97
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,000
And at the top, you will have the option to select Update now.

98
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,000
Or click on Theme details and at the top, you will also be able to update.

99
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,000
And lastly, you also have the option to enable auto updates for this specific theme.

100
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:47,000
How do I delete a theme?

101
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,000
To delete a theme, select the relevant theme and at the bottom right, you will have the option to delete.

102
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,000
And lastly, how do I get support?

103
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,000
To get support, make your way to the theme directory, select the relevant theme and scroll down to support.

104
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:10,000
The best way to get help with a theme is by going to the theme's related support forum to ask questions or view other tickets.

105
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:19,000
I trust you will find the right theme that meets all your needs.

